WEBVTT

00:02.135 --> 00:03.970
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.970 --> 00:06.406
HE'S ON LIFE SUPPORT.
LIFE SUPPORT?!

00:06.406 --> 00:08.174
SHE DOES IT ONE MORE TIME,
I'M GONNA HURT HER.

00:08.174 --> 00:09.643
YOU ALREADY DID.

00:09.643 --> 00:11.612
JEFFERY TOLD US HE'S GAY.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.013
EVERYBODY KNOWS, DAVID.

00:13.013 --> 00:15.115
HOW COULD YOU LOSE MY CAR?
WERE YOU THAT HIGH?

00:15.115 --> 00:16.817
HUH?

00:16.817 --> 00:18.685
ANSWER ME!

00:18.685 --> 00:20.253
JEFFERY, I HAD A WRECK.

00:20.253 --> 00:21.755
WHAT?!

00:21.755 --> 00:24.424
I KNOW
YOU'RE ON DIALYSIS, TONY.

00:24.424 --> 00:26.927
YEAH.
HE CAN GIVE ME HIS KIDNEYS.

00:26.927 --> 00:30.030
I WANT YOU TO GO TO HELL.

00:44.811 --> 00:46.780
HI!
HI!

00:46.780 --> 00:49.149
IS THAT JEFFERY
IN THE SHOWER?

00:49.149 --> 00:50.150
YEAH.

00:50.150 --> 00:51.652
YOU KNOW,
I HAVE TO TELL YOU,

00:51.652 --> 00:53.654
IT'S WEIRD HAVING A GUY
LIVE HERE WITH US.

00:53.654 --> 00:55.355
IT'S FINE.

00:55.355 --> 00:57.691
WELL,
WHEN IS HE GONNA LEAVE?

00:57.691 --> 01:01.568
HE'S FIGURING SOME STUFF OUT,
AND THEN HE'LL GO.

01:01.568 --> 01:03.336
GREAT.

01:03.336 --> 01:06.306
YOU MUST HAVE GOTTEN IN
LATE LAST NIGHT.

01:06.306 --> 01:08.407
UH, YEAH.

01:08.407 --> 01:11.244
MM. THANKS.

01:11.244 --> 01:12.846
WHERE'D YOU GO?

01:12.846 --> 01:15.649
UM...

01:15.649 --> 01:17.017
I WENT AND SAW A MOVIE.

01:17.017 --> 01:19.753
OH!
SEE ANYTHING GOOD?

01:19.753 --> 01:22.689
YEAH.

01:22.689 --> 01:25.559
WHAT DID YOU SEE?
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:28.161 --> 01:29.696
WHAT?

01:29.696 --> 01:31.031
NOTHING.

01:31.031 --> 01:33.900
I HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM MY PARENTS.

01:33.900 --> 01:36.937
NO?
NO. NOT A WORD.

01:36.937 --> 01:38.204
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THEY'RE DOING?

01:38.204 --> 01:41.074
TRYING TO FIGURE
THIS LAWSUIT OUT.

01:41.074 --> 01:43.243
WE DRAFTED IT.
DO YOU THINK MY DAD NOTICES?

01:43.243 --> 01:45.478
WELL, IT WASN'T THAT
WE WERE GONNA SUE THEM.

01:45.478 --> 01:47.180
IT WAS THE THREAT
OF THE LAWSUIT

01:47.180 --> 01:49.215
THAT WAS SUPPOSED TO
GET THEM TO REACT.

01:49.215 --> 01:51.718
WELL, HE'S NOT BUYING IT.

01:51.718 --> 01:52.919
HE WILL.

01:52.919 --> 01:54.555
ARE YOU SURE?
MM‐HMM.

01:54.555 --> 01:57.057
WE NEED TO JUST TURN UP
THE HEAT A LITTLE BIT.

01:57.057 --> 01:58.424
HOW?

01:58.424 --> 02:01.267
I HAVE A FEW IDEAS.

02:01.267 --> 02:02.736
MM‐KAY.
YEAH.

02:02.736 --> 02:03.970
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU.

02:03.970 --> 02:05.606
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

02:05.606 --> 02:08.942
OH. I SAW THIS PLACE ONLINE
I WAS GONNA GO VISIT.

02:08.942 --> 02:10.143
OH.

02:10.143 --> 02:12.178
DESIGN FOR THE ART.

02:12.178 --> 02:14.047
THAT SOUNDS NICE.

02:14.047 --> 02:15.215
YEAH.

02:15.215 --> 02:17.083
YOU SEEM REALLY HAPPY.

02:17.083 --> 02:19.218
YES, I AM.

02:19.218 --> 02:21.221
YOU SEE WHAT
INDEPENDENCE CAN DO.

02:21.221 --> 02:23.790
YEAH. I LOVE IT.

02:23.790 --> 02:25.158
IT'S POWERFUL.

02:25.158 --> 02:27.728
WE GOT TO GET MY PARENTS
TO GIVE ME THAT MONEY.

02:27.728 --> 02:29.162
THEY WILL.

02:29.162 --> 02:30.831
ARE YOU SURE?

02:30.831 --> 02:32.232
YES.

02:32.232 --> 02:35.235
OKAY. I GOT TO GO.

02:35.235 --> 02:37.771
WAIT. AMANDA.
YEAH?

02:37.771 --> 02:41.407
HAVE YOU SEEN
PROFESSOR CANON?

02:41.407 --> 02:43.143
NO.

02:43.143 --> 02:44.811
AMANDA?

02:44.811 --> 02:46.680
NO, I HAVEN'T.

02:46.680 --> 02:48.815
WHY WOULD I SEE HIM
AFTER WHAT HE DID?

02:48.815 --> 02:50.116
OKAY.

02:50.116 --> 02:51.752
WHY?

02:51.752 --> 02:53.954
I WAS JUST WONDERING.

02:53.954 --> 02:56.557
YOU KNOW HE'S...DANGEROUS.

02:56.557 --> 02:58.592
YEAH.

02:58.592 --> 03:00.233
YEAH. OKAY.

03:01.668 --> 03:03.169
OKAY.

03:03.169 --> 03:04.971
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

03:04.971 --> 03:08.008
YEAH. FINE.

03:08.008 --> 03:09.710
OKAY.

03:09.710 --> 03:11.111
I'M GONNA GO.

03:11.111 --> 03:13.914
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

03:21.487 --> 03:24.057
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:28.194 --> 03:30.831
"DESIGN FOR THE ART."

03:50.851 --> 03:53.086
[ SIGHS ]

03:53.086 --> 03:54.354
BENNY.

03:54.354 --> 03:55.989
COME ON.

04:06.840 --> 04:09.275
CANDACE!

04:09.275 --> 04:11.912
[ SIGHS ] DAMN,
I WISH YOU WERE STRAIGHT.

04:13.013 --> 04:14.615
SORRY.

04:14.615 --> 04:17.217
TAKE YOUR TIME PUTTING
YOUR CLOTHES ON.

04:22.556 --> 04:24.124
DID I HEAR AMANDA?

04:24.124 --> 04:25.425
SHE JUST LEFT.

04:25.425 --> 04:27.193
SHE LEFT?
MM‐HMM.

04:27.193 --> 04:29.329
WHERE'S SHE GOING
SO EARLY IN THE MORNING?

04:29.329 --> 04:30.363
SHE QUIT LAW SCHOOL.

04:30.363 --> 04:32.032
SHE'S FINE.

04:33.166 --> 04:34.968
I'M WORRIED ABOUT HER.

04:34.968 --> 04:36.803
JEFFERY, SHE'S FINE.

04:36.803 --> 04:38.037
NO, SHE'S NOT.

04:38.037 --> 04:39.138
YES, SHE IS.

04:39.138 --> 04:41.775
CANDACE, YOU DON'T KNOW
HOW THIS WORKS.

04:41.775 --> 04:42.943
YOU SLOWLY GET WORSE.

04:42.943 --> 04:44.210
THAT GIRL IS NOT CRAZY.

04:44.210 --> 04:46.880
NO, SHE'S NOT CRAZY.
SHE'S MENTALLY ILL.

04:46.880 --> 04:50.416
SHE HAS SPENT HER ENTIRE LIFE
HOLDING EVERY DAMN THING IN.

04:50.416 --> 04:51.818
SHE'S FINE.

04:51.818 --> 04:53.920
THAT WOULD MAKE ME CRAZY, TOO.
LET HER GET IT OUT.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.321
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE,
CANDACE.

04:55.321 --> 04:57.423
YES, IT IS.

04:57.423 --> 05:00.093
[ SIGHS ]
THIS IS ODD.

05:00.093 --> 05:01.434
WHAT?

05:01.434 --> 05:03.970
MY BROTHER'S
NOT ANSWERING MY CALLS.

05:03.970 --> 05:05.739
MAYBE HE'S BUSY.

05:05.739 --> 05:08.408
NO.
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT.

05:08.408 --> 05:10.476
WHY DON'T YOU JUST CALL HIM
AT WORK?

05:10.476 --> 05:13.980
HE'S A TOW‐TRUCK DRIVER.
HIS CELL IS HIS JOB.

05:13.980 --> 05:15.015
TOW‐TRUCK DRIVER?

05:15.015 --> 05:17.250
YES.
AND HE LOVES WHAT HE DOES.

05:17.250 --> 05:19.419
I'M GONNA GO CHECK ON HIM.

05:19.419 --> 05:20.854
WOW, YOU'RE THAT WORRIED?

05:20.854 --> 05:23.023
YEAH, THIS IS NOT LIKE HIM.

05:23.023 --> 05:25.125
WANT ME TO GO WITH YOU?
NO.

05:25.125 --> 05:28.261
BUT I HATE TALKING
TO MY MOTHER.

05:29.663 --> 05:30.764
WAIT A MINUTE.

05:30.764 --> 05:32.165
THE MOTHER
THAT WAS MURDERED

05:32.165 --> 05:33.399
AND WAS THE REASON

05:33.399 --> 05:35.502
WHY YOU'RE IN THE
WITNESS‐PROTECTION PROGRAM?

05:35.502 --> 05:37.337
THAT'S WHO
YOU'RE GONNA TALK TO?

05:37.337 --> 05:39.640
MY MOTHER IS HANNA.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.375
WAIT.
THE CRYERS' MAID?

05:42.375 --> 05:43.644
YES.

05:45.111 --> 05:47.480
OH. WOW.
THAT'S YOUR MOTHER?

05:47.480 --> 05:49.516
YES. NOW LET IT GO.

05:49.516 --> 05:50.851
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TALK TO HER

05:50.851 --> 05:52.485
IF YOU WANT TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE YOUR BROTHER IS.

05:52.485 --> 05:55.722
YES. I KNOW THAT,
UNFORTUNATELY.

05:55.722 --> 05:58.559
LISTEN, YOU HAVE TO GET OFF
THAT COUCH AND GO GET A JOB.

05:58.559 --> 06:00.834
I'M WORKING ON IT.

06:00.834 --> 06:02.468
GOOD.

06:02.468 --> 06:04.705
OKAY. YOU'RE TIRED OF ME
ALREADY. I GOT IT.

06:04.705 --> 06:07.774
NO, I'M TIRED OF SEEING YOU
IN THOSE SAME CLOTHES.

06:07.774 --> 06:08.875
AH.

06:08.875 --> 06:11.211
AND I THINK YOU SHOULD
GET IN THE FIGHT.

06:11.211 --> 06:13.880
[ SIGHS ] I AM.

06:13.880 --> 06:17.217
GOOD.
BECAUSE I MAY BE MOVING.

06:17.217 --> 06:18.552
MOVING?!

06:18.552 --> 06:19.820
YEAH.

06:19.820 --> 06:23.957
I'M GONNA PASS THE BAR SOON,

06:23.957 --> 06:27.694
AND I'M THINKING ABOUT MOVING
TO ATLANTA TO START OVER.

06:27.694 --> 06:29.896
REALLY?
YEAH.

06:29.896 --> 06:31.932
WOW. THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

06:31.932 --> 06:33.867
YOU SHOULD COME WITH ME.

06:33.867 --> 06:36.469
REALLY?
MM‐HMM.

06:36.469 --> 06:38.872
YEAH,
GET OUT OF THIS PLACE.

06:38.872 --> 06:40.574
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

06:40.574 --> 06:41.742
I KNOW I AM.

06:41.742 --> 06:44.344
THIS PLACE IS GETTING
TOO SMALL FOR ME.

06:44.344 --> 06:46.279
BUT WHAT ABOUT AMANDA?

06:46.279 --> 06:48.615
SHE'LL COME, TOO.

06:48.615 --> 06:49.950
REALLY?

06:49.950 --> 06:51.752
YEAH.

06:51.752 --> 06:53.987
WE'LL BOTH
KEEP AN EYE ON HER.

06:53.987 --> 06:54.988
OKAY.

06:54.988 --> 06:56.557
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

06:56.557 --> 07:00.026
YOU THINK ABOUT IT.
AND START LOOKING FOR A JOB.

07:03.136 --> 07:04.838
HERE.

07:04.838 --> 07:07.407
THANK YOU.
MM‐HMM.

07:11.878 --> 07:12.879
WOW.

07:12.879 --> 07:14.648
WHAT?
THIS IS SO SAD.

07:14.648 --> 07:17.250
WHAT?

07:17.250 --> 07:20.754
"LITTLE GIRL KILLED
BY A HIT‐AND‐RUN DRIVER."

07:20.754 --> 07:23.256
YEAH,
I HEARD ABOUT THAT.

07:23.256 --> 07:25.291
MAN, SOME PEOPLE
ARE SO CRUEL.

07:25.291 --> 07:27.260
AND THEY JUST LEFT HER
THERE.

07:27.260 --> 07:28.762
I MEAN... [ SCOFFS ]

07:28.762 --> 07:31.331
AND HERE, LOOK, IT SAYS
THEY HIT ANOTHER GUY, TOO.

07:31.331 --> 07:32.398
HMM.

07:32.398 --> 07:34.300
I GOT TO GO CHECK
ON MY BROTHER.

07:34.300 --> 07:35.669
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL SEE YOU.

07:35.669 --> 07:37.470
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
GOOD LUCK.

07:37.470 --> 07:38.772
THANKS.

07:48.849 --> 07:50.617
OH, MY GOD.

07:53.186 --> 07:55.689
BLACK SEDAN.

08:05.205 --> 08:07.407
JIM, I JUST LEFT THE COURTROOM
LOOKING FOR YOU.

08:07.407 --> 08:08.542
MAGGIE'S WAITING ON YOU.

08:08.542 --> 08:10.443
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M GOING
THROUGH, DAVID.

08:10.443 --> 08:11.878
DID YOU GET
THE INFORMATION?

08:11.878 --> 08:13.079
NO.
DAMN IT, DAVID.

08:13.079 --> 08:14.548
LOOK, VERONICA
WOULDN'T GIVE IT TO ME,

08:14.548 --> 08:15.949
AND I HAVEN'T BEEN
ABLE TO FIND IT.

08:15.949 --> 08:17.718
WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH THAT WIFE OF YOURS?

08:17.718 --> 08:19.019
LEAVE MY WIFE
OUT OF THIS.

08:19.019 --> 08:20.887
YOUR WIFE IS IN THIS.
SHE'S IN THIS UP TO HERE.

08:20.887 --> 08:22.322
WE ALL ARE.

08:22.322 --> 08:25.291
COME ON. MAGGIE'S WAITING
IN YOUR OFFICE.

08:25.291 --> 08:26.760
OKAY.

08:26.760 --> 08:29.229
THANKS.

08:29.229 --> 08:31.331
THERE HE IS.

08:31.331 --> 08:33.166
HI, JIM.
HI, MAGGIE.

08:33.166 --> 08:35.468
YOU'RE LATE.
YES, I'M LATE.

08:35.468 --> 08:37.571
DAVID, YOU SHOULD SIT
NEXT TO THE GOVERNOR.

08:37.571 --> 08:39.272
ALWAYS SIT
NEXT TO THE GOVERNOR.

08:40.641 --> 08:42.676
ARE YOU OKAY?

08:45.579 --> 08:48.014
I'M FINE.

08:48.014 --> 08:49.716
OKAY.

08:50.817 --> 08:52.285
WE HAVE A BIT OF A PROBLEM,

08:52.285 --> 08:55.188
BUT I THINK WE CAN TURN THAT
INTO A GREAT OPPORTUNITY.

08:55.188 --> 08:57.323
WHAT'S THAT?

08:57.323 --> 08:59.860
WELL, I KNOW THAT YOU BOTH
WANTED TO ANNOUNCE IMMEDIATELY,

08:59.860 --> 09:01.935
BUT I THINK WE SHOULD
PUSH IT BACK A FEW DAYS.

09:01.935 --> 09:06.006
WHY? THE OTHER CANDIDATE'S
ALREADY ANNOUNCING.

09:06.006 --> 09:07.741
I KNOW, AND I THINK
THAT'S A MISTAKE.

09:07.741 --> 09:09.209
HOW SO?

09:09.209 --> 09:10.811
THEY'RE MISSING
THE PULSE OF THE PEOPLE.

09:10.811 --> 09:11.912
THERE'S A COMMUNITY UPRISING

09:11.912 --> 09:13.313
OVER THE DEATH
OF THIS LITTLE GIRL,

09:13.313 --> 09:14.615
AND IT'S GONNA ROCK
THIS TOWN.

09:14.615 --> 09:16.583
YOU REALLY THINK IT'S GONNA
BE THAT BIG OF A DEAL?

09:16.583 --> 09:18.284
OH, ABSOLUTELY.
DON'T YOU THINK SO?

09:18.284 --> 09:20.721
NO.

09:20.721 --> 09:22.388
COME ON, JIM.

09:23.289 --> 09:26.359
YOU GUYS NEED TO BE ON THE PULSE
OF WHAT'S GOING ON.

09:28.461 --> 09:30.864
WE'LL BE ON THE PULSE
FOR YOU, OKAY?

09:30.864 --> 09:32.098
WE'RE GONNA MAKE THIS
WORK FOR US.

09:32.098 --> 09:34.668
HOW ARE YOU
GOING TO DO THAT?

09:37.203 --> 09:39.372
THIS LITTLE GIRL
HAS BEEN ON THE FRONT PAGE

09:39.372 --> 09:41.141
OF EVERY NEWSPAPER
IN THIS STATE,

09:41.141 --> 09:43.209
AND IT'S STARTING TO MAKE
NATIONAL NEWS.

09:43.209 --> 09:44.878
YES, I'VE NOTICED.

09:44.878 --> 09:45.879
YEAH, SO YOUR ANNOUNCEMENT

09:45.879 --> 09:47.280
SHOULDN'T COME
IN THE MIDDLE OF THIS.

09:47.280 --> 09:50.584
YOU'RE GONNA LET
THE OTHER GUYS LOOK INSENSITIVE,

09:50.584 --> 09:53.319
AND YOU TWO ‐‐ YOU'RE GONNA
TAKE A DIFFERENT ROUTE.

09:53.319 --> 09:55.589
WHICH ROUTE IS THAT?

09:55.589 --> 10:00.066
YOU'RE GONNA STAND
WITH THE FAMILY.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.136
IS THAT SO?

10:04.771 --> 10:05.839
YES.

10:05.839 --> 10:07.841
IT'S A BRILLIANT MOVE.
DON'T YOU THINK?

10:07.841 --> 10:10.611
[ CHUCKLES ]
YES.

10:10.611 --> 10:12.478
I AGREE.

10:14.080 --> 10:15.882
DO YOU, JUDGE CRYER?

10:20.486 --> 10:22.322
YES. I DO.

10:23.824 --> 10:25.258
GREAT.

10:25.258 --> 10:28.228
I ALSO THINK THAT WE SHOULD
ISSUE A STATEMENT OF SUPPORT

10:28.228 --> 10:29.295
FOR THE POLICE,

10:29.295 --> 10:31.832
MAKING SURE THAT THEY CATCH
THE DRIVER

10:31.832 --> 10:33.366
WHO KILLED
THIS LITTLE GIRL.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.368
I CAN HAVE THE PUBLICIST
DRAFT SOMETHING.

10:35.368 --> 10:36.436
ARE YOU BOTH ON BOARD?

10:36.436 --> 10:37.738
YES, DO IT.

10:37.738 --> 10:40.040
IT NEEDS TO BE
FROM THE BOTH OF YOU.

10:40.040 --> 10:42.008
ARE YOU BOTH ON BOARD?

10:42.008 --> 10:44.044
YEAH. WE CAN DO THAT.

10:44.044 --> 10:45.646
GREAT. AND HER FUNERAL
IS THIS AFTERNOON.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.047
I THINK YOU BOTH
SHOULD BE THERE.

10:50.083 --> 10:51.518
WHAT?
THE FUNERAL.

10:51.518 --> 10:54.287
I THINK YOU SHOULD GO,
SHOW THE COMMUNITY
THAT YOU SUPPORT THEM.

10:54.287 --> 10:56.356
NO, NO. A FUNERAL'S
A VERY PRIVATE MATTER.

10:56.356 --> 10:58.224
I DON'T THINK
THAT WE SHOULD INTRUDE.

10:58.224 --> 11:01.134
OKAY, LISTEN, JIM, YOU HIRED ME
BECAUSE I'M THE BEST, OKAY?

11:01.134 --> 11:02.335
AND THIS IS WHAT
YOU NEED TO DO.

11:02.335 --> 11:03.570
TRUST ME.

11:03.570 --> 11:05.471
YOU NEED TO BE AS OUTRAGED
AS EVERYONE ELSE.

11:06.940 --> 11:09.475
OF COURSE WE ARE.

11:11.745 --> 11:13.413
OKAY. GREAT.
I'LL MAKE THE ARRANGEMENTS.

11:13.413 --> 11:15.015
NOW, THERE'LL BE
A LOT OF PRESS THERE,

11:15.015 --> 11:17.183
SO MAKE SURE THAT YOU KEEP
YOUR ANSWERS SHORT AND PRECISE.

11:17.183 --> 11:19.019
RIGHT.
I'LL CALL YOUR WIVES.

11:19.019 --> 11:21.021
WHAT?
YOUR WIVES.

11:21.021 --> 11:22.656
WHY?

11:22.656 --> 11:25.425
FAMILY, JIM. COME ON.
ALWAYS THINK FAMILY.

11:25.425 --> 11:27.293
CAN YOUR SON GO?

11:28.895 --> 11:31.297
NO.

11:31.297 --> 11:33.534
HOW ABOUT YOUR CHILDREN?

11:33.534 --> 11:35.435
WHAT? NO.

11:35.435 --> 11:37.804
ARE YOU SURE? IT WOULD
BE SO GREAT TO HAVE
THE ENTIRE FAMILY THERE ‐‐

11:37.804 --> 11:39.873
NO, MY CHILDREN ARE NOT
GOING TO THE FUNERAL, MAGGIE.

11:39.873 --> 11:41.007
OKAY.
THEY'RE NOT.

11:41.007 --> 11:42.876
ALL RIGHT, FINE.
I'LL SETTLE FOR YOUR WIVES.

11:42.876 --> 11:45.111
FINE.

11:45.111 --> 11:48.114
MM.

11:48.114 --> 11:51.685
YOU TWO MAKE
A HANDSOME PICTURE.

11:51.685 --> 11:53.787
TRY TO GET NEAR
SOME OF THE NEIGHBORHOOD KIDS.

11:53.787 --> 11:56.990
GREAT PHOTO OPS.
SURE, WE CAN DO THAT.

11:56.990 --> 11:58.792
OKAY, I'LL BE IN TOUCH
WITHIN THE HOUR.

11:58.792 --> 12:01.301
I'M GOING TO LOOK AT A SPACE
TO RUN THIS CAMPAIGN OUT OF.

12:01.301 --> 12:03.469
AND, YOU KNOW, WE NEED TO DO
A FUNDRAISER DINNER

12:03.469 --> 12:04.605
SOONER RATHER THAN LATER.

12:04.605 --> 12:06.006
YOU TWO
ARE A LITTLE BEHIND.

12:06.006 --> 12:07.574
YES.

12:07.574 --> 12:08.675
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

12:13.580 --> 12:14.615
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

12:14.615 --> 12:16.082
DAVID.
I KNOW.

12:16.082 --> 12:18.552
THE FUNERAL?

12:18.552 --> 12:20.220
I KNOW.

12:29.362 --> 12:31.698
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

12:39.806 --> 12:41.307
CRYER RESIDENCE.

12:41.307 --> 12:42.676
HANNA: Celine.

12:42.676 --> 12:43.844
WHO'S THIS?

12:43.844 --> 12:45.111
[ SIGHS ]

12:45.111 --> 12:46.780
THIS IS HANNA.

12:46.780 --> 12:49.550
OH. HI.
HOW ARE YOU?

12:49.550 --> 12:51.752
IS MRS. CRYER THERE?

12:51.752 --> 12:53.954
NO, SHE'S NOT.

12:53.954 --> 12:56.222
ARE YOU GIVING HER
MY MESSAGES?

12:56.222 --> 12:57.591
YES.

12:57.591 --> 12:59.359
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE GIVING
HER MY MESSAGES?

12:59.359 --> 13:01.134
'CAUSE SHE LEFT ONE FOR ME
ON MY CELLPHONE.

13:01.134 --> 13:02.903
I SAID YES!

13:02.903 --> 13:05.772
LISTEN, CELINE,
MY CELLPHONE IS DEAD.

13:05.772 --> 13:08.675
I'M GET THE CHARGER
IN A LITTLE WHILE,

13:08.675 --> 13:11.377
BUT [SIGHS]
I NEED TO TALK TO HER.

13:11.377 --> 13:12.613
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

13:12.613 --> 13:14.014
OKAY.
Okay.

13:14.014 --> 13:15.949
How about "Thank you"?

13:17.083 --> 13:18.552
THANK YOU, CELINE.

13:18.552 --> 13:19.986
YOU'RE WELCOME.

13:19.986 --> 13:21.622
Wait.

13:21.622 --> 13:23.256
WHAT?

13:23.256 --> 13:24.591
WHERE ARE YOU?

13:24.591 --> 13:27.961
I TOLD YOU,
I'M HAVING A FAMILY EMERGENCY.

13:27.961 --> 13:29.796
OH.
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

13:29.796 --> 13:31.565
OH, DON'T ACT LIKE
YOU CARE, CELINE.

13:31.565 --> 13:34.334
HANNA! I DO CARE.

13:34.334 --> 13:35.969
LISTEN, JUST TELL HER
THAT I CALLED

13:35.969 --> 13:37.370
AND IF SHE NEEDS
TO REACH ME

13:37.370 --> 13:39.239
TO CALL ME ON MY CELL
ANYTIME AFTER 4:00.

13:39.239 --> 13:42.576
OF COURSE. IS THAT ALL?

13:42.576 --> 13:46.647
TELL HER I MIGHT NEED
A COUPLE MORE DAYS OFF.

13:46.647 --> 13:48.181
OOH. A COUPLE DAYS?

13:48.181 --> 13:50.784
ARE YOU SURE
EVERYTHING'S OKAY?

13:50.784 --> 13:52.318
Hanna,
you don't sound good.

13:52.318 --> 13:54.788
CELINE, LISTEN, IF YOU DON'T
GIVE HER THE MESSAGES,

13:54.788 --> 13:56.590
YOU KNOW SHE'S GONNA BE
TICKED OFF.

13:56.590 --> 13:58.992
I KNOW. WITH YOU.

13:58.992 --> 14:01.001
NO. YOU.

14:01.001 --> 14:02.869
HANNA, LOOK,
I ALREADY TOLD YOU.

14:02.869 --> 14:04.170
I GAVE HER THE MESSAGES.

14:04.170 --> 14:07.373
JUST MAKE SURE YOU GIVE HER
THE MESSAGE.

14:07.373 --> 14:12.646
OR WHAT? ARE YOU GOING TO FIRE
ME, MISS CHIEF OF STAFF?

14:12.646 --> 14:14.815
WE WEAR THE SAME
MAID'S UNIFORM, YOU KNOW.

14:14.815 --> 14:16.149
GIVE HER THE MESSAGES,
OR ELSE SHE ‐‐

14:16.149 --> 14:18.619
OH, PLEASE.
YOU CAN'T FIRE ME.

14:18.619 --> 14:19.786
NO, BUT SHE CAN.

14:19.786 --> 14:22.789
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE, DARLING.

14:22.789 --> 14:25.125
YOU KNOW I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS.

14:25.125 --> 14:26.292
THANK YOU.

14:33.466 --> 14:35.736
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

14:48.915 --> 14:50.717
SO, THIS IS IT.

14:50.717 --> 14:52.519
IT'S REALLY NICE.

14:52.519 --> 14:54.988
I'LL MAKE SURE TO TELL
THE LANDLORD YOU THINK SO.

14:56.590 --> 14:58.692
THIS CAN BE JIM'S OFFICE.

14:58.692 --> 15:01.735
AND WE CAN USE
THIS ONE FOR DAVID.

15:01.735 --> 15:03.904
ARE THERE
ANY OTHER OFFICES?

15:03.904 --> 15:05.572
YEAH, YEAH, THERE'S SEVERAL MORE
RIGHT THROUGH THERE.

15:05.572 --> 15:06.940
YEAH?
YEAH.

15:06.940 --> 15:09.776
OH, THIS IS GREAT. YEAH, WE
COULD TOTALLY WORK WITH THIS.

15:09.776 --> 15:11.545
IF YOU DON'T MIND ME ASKING,

15:11.545 --> 15:14.180
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
USING THE OFFICES FOR?

15:14.180 --> 15:16.683
WELL, JUDGE JIM CRYER
AND DAVID HARRINGTON

15:16.683 --> 15:19.786
ARE RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR, SO
WE NEED CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS.

15:19.786 --> 15:20.921
REALLY?

15:20.921 --> 15:24.891
YEAH. AND I THINK
THIS COULD BE THE PLACE.

15:24.891 --> 15:26.292
JIM CRYER?

15:26.292 --> 15:27.528
YES.

15:27.528 --> 15:29.630
SO, HE'LL BE HERE?

15:29.630 --> 15:31.431
YES.

15:31.431 --> 15:32.799
WOW, WELL, I‐I REALLY HOPE

15:32.799 --> 15:35.268
THAT MY BOSS RENTS
THIS PLACE OUT TO YOU GUYS.

15:35.268 --> 15:37.871
I'M SURE HE WILL.

15:37.871 --> 15:40.841
LISTEN, IF ‐‐ IF I WANTED TO
GET INVOLVED IN YOUR CAMPAIGN,

15:40.841 --> 15:42.643
HOW WOULD I GO ABOUT
DOING THAT?

15:42.643 --> 15:44.377
WELL,
YOU COULD VOLUNTEER.

15:44.377 --> 15:45.879
I JUST VOLUNTEER?
THAT'S IT.

15:45.879 --> 15:48.381
OH, ABSOLUTELY.
WE CAN ALWAYS USE VOLUNTEERS.

15:48.381 --> 15:51.117
OKAY.
I'LL LOOK INTO THAT.

15:51.117 --> 15:53.019
WELL, HELP US
GET THE BUILDING FIRST,

15:53.019 --> 15:54.821
AND THEN WE'LL TAKE IT
FROM THERE.

15:54.821 --> 15:56.957
OH, I'LL MAKE SURE
YOU GUYS GET THE BUILDING.

15:56.957 --> 15:58.625
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
OH, GOD, I'M SORRY.

15:58.625 --> 16:00.293
EXCUSE ME ONE MOMENT.
HELLO.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.803
YOU PHONED, MAGGIE?

16:02.803 --> 16:04.605
YES, HI, KATHERYN.
I'M SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,

16:04.605 --> 16:05.872
BUT I WANTED TO
LET YOU KNOW

16:05.872 --> 16:07.340
I SPOKE TO JIM AND DAVID
EARLIER,

16:07.340 --> 16:09.342
AND I TOLD THEM THAT
THE FAMILY SHOULD BE PRESENT

16:09.342 --> 16:10.811
AT THE FUNERAL
OF LIZZIE CASTILLE.

16:10.811 --> 16:12.278
YOU KNOW,
THE LITTLE GIRL ‐‐

16:12.278 --> 16:13.313
YES. I KNOW.

16:13.313 --> 16:14.515
Right.

16:14.515 --> 16:17.083
Well, you and your children
should come.

16:17.083 --> 16:18.685
EXCUSE ME?

16:18.685 --> 16:20.854
I SPOKE TO JIM EARLIER.

16:20.854 --> 16:22.188
[ SCOFFS ]

16:22.188 --> 16:24.224
HE SAID IT WAS OKAY
TO BRING THE CHILDREN?

16:25.759 --> 16:27.160
YES.

16:27.160 --> 16:28.294
I don't think so.

16:28.294 --> 16:29.563
NO? WHY NOT?

16:30.731 --> 16:33.867
WYATT AND AMANDA WILL NOT BE
SUBJECT TO A FUNERAL, MAGGIE.

16:33.867 --> 16:35.368
Do you understand?

16:35.368 --> 16:36.570
I'm sorry.

16:36.570 --> 16:38.304
OKAY.
WELL, YOU NEED TO BE THERE.

16:38.304 --> 16:39.840
ME?

16:39.840 --> 16:41.474
YES.
YOU SHOULD ACCOMPANY JIM.

16:42.543 --> 16:43.677
MAGGIE, I ‐‐

16:43.677 --> 16:44.878
LISTEN,
WE'RE IN THE CAMPAIGN

16:44.878 --> 16:46.346
EVEN THOUGH WE HAVEN'T
ANNOUNCED YET.

16:46.346 --> 16:48.949
You really should be
by his side.

16:50.483 --> 16:51.752
ALL RIGHT.

16:51.752 --> 16:53.419
Good. Thank you.

16:55.055 --> 16:58.324
OH, AND CAN YOU CALL
MRS. HARRINGTON?

16:58.324 --> 17:00.126
She should be there,
as well.

17:00.126 --> 17:01.535
OH, I WILL.

17:10.176 --> 17:12.078
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY OFFICE?

17:12.078 --> 17:14.047
YOU DON'T RETURN
PHONE CALLS.

17:14.047 --> 17:15.481
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS, CANDACE.

17:15.481 --> 17:17.751
YOU DIDN'T RESPOND
TO THE LAWSUIT.

17:17.751 --> 17:19.520
NICE TRY.
I'LL GIVE YOU A "B."

17:19.520 --> 17:21.187
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

17:21.187 --> 17:23.156
YOU'RE A LAW STUDENT,
CANDACE,

17:23.156 --> 17:26.026
TRYING TO PLAY ALL BIG GIRL
BY FILING A LAWSUIT.

17:26.026 --> 17:28.562
YOU ACTUALLY HAVE TO PASS THE
BAR BEFORE YOU CAN TRY A CASE.

17:28.562 --> 17:30.330
I'M CLOSER TO THAT
THAN YOU THINK.

17:30.330 --> 17:31.698
GET OUT. GO ON.

17:31.698 --> 17:34.500
[ SIGHS ]
DON'T YOU MISS ME?

17:34.500 --> 17:36.236
NOW. LEAVE.

17:36.236 --> 17:37.738
WE MISS YOU.

17:37.738 --> 17:39.472
WHO'S WE?

17:39.472 --> 17:41.107
THE THREE OF US.

17:41.107 --> 17:43.376
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:43.376 --> 17:45.712
ME...

17:45.712 --> 17:47.748
MY BODY...

17:47.748 --> 17:49.516
THE BABY.

17:49.516 --> 17:53.186
I'M GONNA TELL YOU THIS
ONE MORE DAMN TIME.

17:53.186 --> 17:56.056
YOU GET OUT OF MY OFFICE,
AND YOU GET OUT OF HERE NOW.

17:56.056 --> 17:57.591
YOU KNOW YOU WANT ME.

18:01.401 --> 18:02.435
WOW.

18:02.435 --> 18:03.770
"WOW."

18:03.770 --> 18:07.173
THAT'S A FIRST.
EVERYTHING OKAY?

18:07.173 --> 18:09.309
DO YOU NEED
SOME LITTLE BLUE PILLS?

18:09.309 --> 18:13.046
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME WHEN
I TELL YOU THAT WE ARE DONE.

18:16.817 --> 18:18.418
SO, YOU FOUND NUMBER 10.

18:18.418 --> 18:20.654
YES, I FOUND NUMBER 10.
HER NAME IS AMANDA.

18:20.654 --> 18:22.322
SHE HAPPENS TO BE
MY DAUGHTER,

18:22.322 --> 18:25.225
AND AS SOON AS YOU GOT YOUR
CLUTCHES INTO HER, YOU LOST ME.

18:25.225 --> 18:28.061
YOU REALLY LOVE HER.
THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

18:28.061 --> 18:30.597
DADDY'S LOVE.
[ SIGHS ]

18:30.597 --> 18:32.432
MAYBE IF YOU
ACTUALLY HAD ONE,

18:32.432 --> 18:34.300
YOU WOULDN'T BE
SO SCREWED UP.

18:34.300 --> 18:37.938
WELL, YOUR KIDS
ARE SO GREAT.

18:37.938 --> 18:43.677
YOU AND THAT...BEAST DID
A FANTASTIC JOB RAISING THEM.

18:43.677 --> 18:46.179
WHILE YOU WERE BOTH TRYING TO
SHIELD THEM FROM THE WORLD,

18:46.179 --> 18:48.582
YOU DIDN'T GIVE THEM
THE SKILLS THEY NEED

18:48.582 --> 18:50.884
TO LIVE IN A WORLD
WITH PEOPLE LIKE ME.

18:50.884 --> 18:52.118
JIM, THIS IS SO EASY.

18:52.118 --> 18:54.621
IF YOU THINK THAT YOU ARE
GOING TO GET A DIME

18:54.621 --> 18:57.490
OF MY DAUGHTER'S INHERITANCE,
YOU ARE SADLY MISTAKEN.

18:57.490 --> 18:59.192
AND IF YOU THINK I WON'T,
THEN YOU'RE WRONG.

18:59.192 --> 19:00.226
THERE IS NO MONEY!

19:00.226 --> 19:02.168
SHE IS GETTING NO MONEY,
CANDACE!

19:02.168 --> 19:03.203
NO?
NO.

19:03.203 --> 19:05.071
SHE'S MENTALLY UNSTABLE.

19:05.071 --> 19:07.708
THERE'S NOT A JUDGE
IN THE WORLD

19:07.708 --> 19:10.611
THAT WOULD GRANT MY DAUGHTER
A DIME.

19:10.611 --> 19:11.712
SAYS WHO?

19:11.712 --> 19:14.280
SAYS EVERY JUDGE
AND DOCTOR IN THIS STATE.

19:14.280 --> 19:16.049
AND I DO HAPPEN
TO KNOW A FEW.

19:16.049 --> 19:19.119
I KNOW A LOT OF DOCTORS WHO
WILL SAY, "SHE'S JUST FINE."

19:19.119 --> 19:20.987
GET OUT OF MY OFFICE
RIGHT NOW.

19:20.987 --> 19:22.355
PLEASE.

19:22.355 --> 19:24.791
WE ACTUALLY HAVE
A BABY TO DISCUSS.

19:24.791 --> 19:27.961
NOW, CANDACE.
IT'S YOUR FINAL WARNING.

19:27.961 --> 19:29.062
GET OUT!

19:29.062 --> 19:30.531
I COULD STILL GO
TO THE PRESS WITH THIS.

19:30.531 --> 19:33.399
YOU GO TO THE DAMN PRESS.
YOU GO. YOU DO IT.

19:33.399 --> 19:34.968
YOU'VE BEEN THREATENING
LONG ENOUGH.

19:34.968 --> 19:37.037
IT'S TIRED, IT'S OLD,
IT'S PATHETIC, JUST LIKE YOU.

19:37.037 --> 19:38.739
YOU ARE PATHETIC.
YOU HAVE NO POWER.

19:38.739 --> 19:40.006
GO TO THE PRESS,

19:40.006 --> 19:42.543
BUT GET OUT OF MY OFFICE NOW
BEFORE I THROW YOU OUT!

19:42.543 --> 19:44.811
YOU WOULDN'T DARE.

19:44.811 --> 19:48.715
GET OUT
OF MY OFFICE NOW!

19:48.715 --> 19:49.950
GET OUT OF HERE!

19:51.752 --> 19:53.086
YOU'RE A JOKE!

19:53.086 --> 19:55.188
GET OFF OF ME!

19:55.188 --> 19:57.691
GET YOUR PATHETIC, SORRY ASS
OUT OF MY OFFICE, CANDACE!

19:57.691 --> 19:58.725
GET OUT!

19:58.725 --> 20:00.093
OKAY.

20:00.093 --> 20:02.135
OKAY, JIM.

20:02.135 --> 20:04.204
GO TO HELL!

20:12.646 --> 20:14.114
CELINE.

20:15.649 --> 20:16.950
IS WYATT HOME?

20:16.950 --> 20:18.985
YES.
I THINK HE'S IN HIS ROOM.

20:18.985 --> 20:20.687
THANKS.

20:20.687 --> 20:24.424
HMM.
WONDER WHAT THAT'S ABOUT.

20:26.259 --> 20:27.594
WYATT.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.863
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
HEY.

20:29.863 --> 20:31.665
HI.

20:31.665 --> 20:34.000
I KNEW YOU'D COME.

20:34.000 --> 20:35.969
WHAT?

20:37.838 --> 20:40.140
WHEN YOU LEFT, I...

20:41.942 --> 20:44.310
...I KNEW
THAT YOU STILL CARED.

20:47.814 --> 20:49.650
YOU WOULD BE WRONG.

20:49.650 --> 20:51.652
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

20:55.556 --> 20:56.857
DID YOU DO THIS?

20:56.857 --> 20:59.826
HUH?

21:02.468 --> 21:04.470
ANSWER ME.

21:07.107 --> 21:08.341
I DON'T KNOW.

21:08.341 --> 21:10.243
WYATT,
DON'T GIVE ME THAT.

21:10.243 --> 21:12.045
JEFFERY.

21:15.949 --> 21:17.651
IS THIS MY CAR?

21:21.522 --> 21:23.657
YEAH.

21:23.657 --> 21:25.626
WHERE IS IT?

21:33.634 --> 21:35.602
I DON'T KNOW.

21:35.602 --> 21:38.138
WYATT, THEY HAVE
A PARTIAL PLATE NUMBER

21:38.138 --> 21:39.540
THAT IS PARTIALLY MINE

21:39.540 --> 21:43.510
AND A DESCRIPTION OF A GUY
THAT SOUNDS A LOT LIKE YOU.

21:46.479 --> 21:47.748
I KNOW.

21:47.748 --> 21:49.516
JEFFERY, WAIT.

21:49.516 --> 21:51.451
YOU CAN'T TURN ME IN.

21:51.451 --> 21:53.854
PLEASE, MAN.

21:53.854 --> 21:57.423
JEFFERY...
YOU CAN'T DO THAT TO ME.

21:58.959 --> 22:00.460
WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:00.460 --> 22:03.069
I KNOW I'VE BEEN AN ASS.

22:03.069 --> 22:05.238
I'M SORRY.

22:06.873 --> 22:09.142
PLEASE DON'T TURN ME IN.

22:10.343 --> 22:12.646
WYATT...

22:12.646 --> 22:15.882
JEFFERY, I MADE A LOT
OF MISTAKES.

22:18.484 --> 22:20.420
BUT THIS ONE ‐‐

22:20.420 --> 22:24.057
I MEAN, JEFFERY,
I KILLED THAT GIRL.

22:24.057 --> 22:25.926
[ Voice breaking ] I...

22:28.962 --> 22:30.931
I'M SORRY, MAN.

22:30.931 --> 22:32.799
I'M SORRY.

22:38.772 --> 22:41.675
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

22:41.675 --> 22:43.744
IT'S OKAY.

22:44.745 --> 22:46.780
OKAY, MAN.

22:46.780 --> 22:49.049
[ SNIFFLES ]

22:51.351 --> 22:52.986
[ SIGHS ]

23:01.167 --> 23:03.303
I'M SORRY.

23:05.405 --> 23:08.141
IF I COULD HAVE
THAT NIGHT BACK,

23:08.141 --> 23:11.311
I WOULD TAKE
THAT NIGHT BACK.

23:11.311 --> 23:12.946
DO YOUR PARENTS KNOW?

23:12.946 --> 23:14.781
YES.

23:14.781 --> 23:17.250
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

23:19.920 --> 23:21.822
JUST SAID
NOT TO TELL ANYBODY.

23:23.223 --> 23:26.693
HAVE YOU SAID ANYTHING
TO ANYBODY?

23:29.295 --> 23:30.931
NO.

23:34.034 --> 23:35.168
OKAY.

23:35.168 --> 23:36.870
JEFFERY...

23:38.171 --> 23:40.674
...PLEASE DON'T TURN ME IN,
OKAY?

23:42.475 --> 23:45.045
I'M NOT GONNA TURN YOU IN,
WYATT.

23:48.414 --> 23:50.551
I WON'T.

23:50.551 --> 23:52.919
THANK YOU, JEFFERY.

23:52.919 --> 23:54.988
YEAH.
THANK YOU.

23:58.625 --> 24:00.466
AND I HIT
THAT TOW‐TRUCK DRIVER.

24:04.437 --> 24:06.973
"TOW‐TRUCK DRIVER"?

24:11.612 --> 24:13.780
I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

24:18.251 --> 24:21.555
I CAN'T GO TO JAIL, MAN.
I CAN'T.

24:21.555 --> 24:25.225
I CAN'T.
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

24:25.225 --> 24:27.561
[ SIGHS ]

24:34.868 --> 24:37.871
THANK YOU.

25:04.170 --> 25:06.306
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

25:09.843 --> 25:11.978
[ KNOCKING CONTINUES ]

25:43.744 --> 25:45.411
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

25:45.411 --> 25:47.480
WHERE IS BENNY?

25:47.480 --> 25:49.015
HE'S NOT HERE.

25:49.015 --> 25:50.617
I CAN SEE THAT.

25:50.617 --> 25:52.152
WHERE IS HE?

25:52.152 --> 25:54.087
WHY?

25:55.421 --> 25:57.958
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU KNOW THIS,
BUT WE TALK EVERY DAY.

25:57.958 --> 25:59.826
WELL, HE'S NOT HERE.

25:59.826 --> 26:02.302
YOU'VE SAID THAT.
WHERE IS HE?

26:02.302 --> 26:03.469
WHERE IS YOUR BABY?

26:03.469 --> 26:04.971
I'M NOT PLAYING
THESE GAMES WITH YOU.

26:04.971 --> 26:06.239
THEN GET ON OUT OF HERE.

26:07.808 --> 26:09.309
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
TO HIM?

26:09.309 --> 26:10.611
WHY?

26:10.611 --> 26:11.845
WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU MEAN, WHY?

26:11.845 --> 26:13.346
WHO YOU TALKING TO?
WAIT A MINUTE.

26:13.346 --> 26:15.148
WATCH YOUR MOUTH.
I'M TALKING TO YOU.

26:15.148 --> 26:16.983
UNH‐UNH.

26:16.983 --> 26:18.519
DID SOMEBODY
DO SOMETHING TO HIM?

26:18.519 --> 26:20.453
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK THAT?

26:20.453 --> 26:22.188
DID YOU DO SOMETHING
TO SOMEBODY ELSE

26:22.188 --> 26:25.526
THAT MIGHT MAKE THEM WANT
TO RETALIATE AGAINST
YOUR BROTHER AGAIN?

26:25.526 --> 26:28.028
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT?

26:28.028 --> 26:30.163
YOU AND YOUR WHORISH WAYS.

26:30.163 --> 26:32.298
MAMA.

26:32.298 --> 26:34.801
ARE YOU SCREWING
THAT WOMAN'S HUSBAND?

26:34.801 --> 26:36.570
WHICH WOMAN?

26:38.204 --> 26:39.640
IS IT REALLY
THAT MANY, CANDACE?

26:39.640 --> 26:41.041
YES. MM‐HMM.

26:41.041 --> 26:43.476
KATHERYN.

26:43.476 --> 26:45.879
"THE BEAST"?

26:45.879 --> 26:47.480
YES. I AM.

26:47.480 --> 26:50.651
I'M SCREWING HER HUSBAND
ALL THE WAY TO THE BANK.

26:50.651 --> 26:53.253
[ SIGHS ]

26:53.253 --> 26:55.088
LITTLE GIRL.

26:56.623 --> 26:58.224
WHERE IS BENNY?

26:58.224 --> 26:59.926
WHERE IS YOUR BABY?

27:01.802 --> 27:03.369
WITH HIS FATHER.

27:03.369 --> 27:05.471
QUINCY?

27:05.471 --> 27:07.874
YES. QUINCY.

27:07.874 --> 27:09.475
YOU'RE LYING.
NO, I'M NOT.

27:09.475 --> 27:10.977
WHERE IS QUINCY?

27:10.977 --> 27:13.046
IN TEXAS.

27:13.046 --> 27:14.581
WHAT'S HE DOING IN TEXAS?

27:14.581 --> 27:16.683
LOOK...

27:16.683 --> 27:19.485
ARE YOU GONNA TELL ME
WHERE BENNY IS OR NOT?

27:19.485 --> 27:21.855
AS SOON AS YOU TELL ME
WHERE YOUR BABY IS.

27:23.724 --> 27:26.026
THIS IS B. S.

27:26.026 --> 27:28.995
YES, IT IS.
GET ON OUT OF HERE, THEN.

27:28.995 --> 27:31.464
THANK YOU.

27:40.373 --> 27:42.509
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

28:00.293 --> 28:02.468
[ WATER RUNNING ]

28:21.722 --> 28:24.057
AH, THOUGHT YOU
WERE GOING TO WORK.

28:25.792 --> 28:28.061
YOU OKAY?

28:28.061 --> 28:30.564
GET THE HELL
OUT OF MY HOUSE.

28:30.564 --> 28:32.265
GET THE HELL
OUT OF MY HOUSE.

28:32.265 --> 28:33.800
Shh!
Woman: HONEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

28:37.170 --> 28:38.238
HONEY?

28:38.238 --> 28:40.306
YEAH, I'M FINE.
[ COUGHS ] FINE.

28:40.306 --> 28:41.842
I HEARD A NOISE.

28:41.842 --> 28:44.410
[ Laughing ] YEAH, I'M A DORK.
I SLIPPED IN THE TUB.

